              The items on 4, 5, and 6 look like some of my common complaint areas.  My new adds : <br><br>1)  I am required to log in to "My Auctions" using my username and password way too often and even if I am still using the site to search.  This to me is an inconvience.<br><br>2) A "Seller Message" system would be nice for a lot of us that manage a lot of auctions.  What I am talking about would be a message that supplies the buyer with the information needed to finish the transaction...This would be sent as one of the old style three emails after winning but only if the seller chooses to use this option for his auctions.<br><br>3) Negative feedbacks to seller or buyer should have to be looked into as there are too many "False" negative feedbacks being left.  <br><br>4) Still waiting for the option to make payments via Paypal as we choose to for early or overdue payments.  This would be a nice option.<br><br>5) A Billing date on the account statement so we know when to expect the deduction from our paypal or credit card account.<br><br>6) If you were to coordinate with Paypal in order to have an "Auto-Insert" option as Ebay as for Paypal logos in all auctions we post.  <br><br>These are rough suggestions and I  know some will not be workable due to other conflicts, but I wanted to lay all my thoughts out there.  <br><br>A Dedicated PlayerAuctions.com Member!<br><br>
